tip: zsh: ^l: clear the screen
%
tip: zsh: ^u: clear command line, saving contents
          ^y: yank saved command
%
tip: zsh: ⌥.: cycle through previous command arguments
%
tip: shell: `fc`: open the last command in $EDITOR, run on exit
%
tip: less: ⇧f: begin following changes to file (same as using `less +F` on the command line)